WEBVTT

00:08.500 --> 00:09.250
[keys clacking]

00:12.041 --> 00:14.792
Okay, so what's the show?
Let's just toss things out.

00:14.792 --> 00:17.000
- What if I'm the president?
- Of what planet?

00:17.000 --> 00:18.500
We'll take it slow.

00:18.500 --> 00:22.500
I will take it
any way you want

00:22.500 --> 00:23.834
to give it to me.

00:23.834 --> 00:25.875
[Beverly] You and Merc?

00:25.875 --> 00:26.834
In fact...

00:26.834 --> 00:29.000
[gasps]
What's this?

00:29.000 --> 00:30.709
I don't know what
I'm gonna tell her.

00:30.709 --> 00:31.500
You're gonna tell her nothing.

00:31.500 --> 00:33.166
That's what
you're gonna tell her.

00:33.166 --> 00:34.583
There's a reason
"hug the messenger"

00:34.583 --> 00:36.333
is not an expression.

00:37.959 --> 00:39.417
Are you okay?

00:39.417 --> 00:40.792
Uh-huh.

00:43.917 --> 00:46.667
[keys clacking]

00:46.667 --> 00:47.792
[typewriter dings]

00:48.792 --> 00:51.917
[wind whooshing]

00:57.583 --> 00:59.583
♪ quirky music ♪

00:59.583 --> 01:05.458
♪♪♪

01:24.041 --> 01:27.125
[gunshot]

01:31.834 --> 01:34.750
♪ quirky music ♪

01:34.750 --> 01:35.709
Hey.

01:35.709 --> 01:37.291
Oh, this is so nice.

01:37.291 --> 01:39.250
I can't remember
the last time we were here.

01:39.250 --> 01:41.709
Or the last time I saw you
in big-girl shoes.

01:41.709 --> 01:44.375
Oh, I know.

01:44.375 --> 01:45.542
My feet were like,

01:45.542 --> 01:47.625
"Are we getting laid
tonight or what?"

01:49.959 --> 01:52.083
By the way, this is on me.

01:52.083 --> 01:53.458
- Oh, no, no, no.
- Yes, yes.

01:53.458 --> 01:55.375
I want to do this.

01:55.375 --> 01:56.959
It's my thank-you lunch.

01:56.959 --> 01:58.166
For?

01:58.166 --> 01:59.083
For being an amazing friend.

01:59.083 --> 02:02.083
Well, I don't know
how amazing--

02:02.083 --> 02:04.083
Bullshit.

02:04.083 --> 02:06.667
I could not have gotten
through this without you.

02:06.667 --> 02:07.417
And Prozac.

02:07.417 --> 02:09.375
- And Prozac.
- And weed.

02:09.375 --> 02:10.417
Well, sure, but...

02:10.417 --> 02:11.959
I can't take weed to lunch.

02:11.959 --> 02:13.792
I'm sure if we went
through your purse,

02:13.792 --> 02:15.000
we'd find that's not true.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.959
I also have
a little bit of--

02:17.959 --> 02:18.792
- Hi.
- Hi.

02:18.792 --> 02:20.375
I'm AJ.

02:20.375 --> 02:21.417
- I'll be your waiter today.
- Yeah, hi, AJ.

02:21.417 --> 02:23.041
- Can you just give us a sec?
- Absolutely.

02:23.041 --> 02:25.458
- Whenever you're ready.
- Thank you.

02:25.458 --> 02:27.500
[chuckles]

02:27.500 --> 02:29.834
I also have
a little bit of news.

02:29.834 --> 02:31.709
- You broke up with Merc.
- What? No.

02:33.000 --> 02:34.125
All right, well, you go.

02:34.125 --> 02:37.667
Actually, that part
is going great.

02:37.667 --> 02:39.709
Great.

02:39.709 --> 02:40.417
I might be pregnant.

02:43.750 --> 02:47.291
God, it feels so weird
to hear it out loud.

02:48.500 --> 02:49.000
I haven't told Merc yet.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.458
You're the first.

02:51.458 --> 02:52.583
Not even my shrink.

02:52.583 --> 02:53.333
He should probably be looped in.

02:55.959 --> 02:57.917
The thing is,
I think--

02:57.917 --> 03:00.250
Okay, do not freak.

03:01.667 --> 03:03.792
I think I want to keep it.

03:03.792 --> 03:04.875
Definitely talk to your shrink.

03:04.875 --> 03:06.166
I know, I know.

03:06.166 --> 03:07.000
I always said
I never wanted one,

03:07.000 --> 03:10.750
but now, I'm thinking...

03:11.667 --> 03:12.959
Why not?

03:12.959 --> 03:14.500
You know?

03:14.500 --> 03:17.166
I mean, I'm almost 37.

03:17.166 --> 03:18.709
- I'm 39.
- Mm-hmm.

03:18.709 --> 03:22.333
And Merc and I are in
such a good place.

03:22.333 --> 03:23.625
Okay.

03:23.625 --> 03:27.583
It's like this was
kind of meant to be.

03:29.041 --> 03:33.583
May I just play
devil's advocate here?

03:34.375 --> 03:36.917
Merc is screwing
Morning Randolph.

03:36.917 --> 03:38.041
What?

03:38.041 --> 03:38.959
And they're engaged.

03:38.959 --> 03:39.834
I'm sorry.

03:39.834 --> 03:42.792
Ooh, tha--

03:42.792 --> 03:44.291
That's not possible.

03:44.291 --> 03:45.375
Not yet, AJ.

03:48.750 --> 03:51.750
I spoke with her.

03:51.750 --> 03:53.250
I saw the ring.

03:53.250 --> 03:55.125
There's a ring?

03:55.125 --> 03:56.667
I'm sorry.

03:57.375 --> 03:59.875
- Is it big?
- Does it matter?

03:59.875 --> 04:00.792
- How big?
- Don't do this to yourself.

04:00.792 --> 04:01.625
How big?

04:01.625 --> 04:03.917
Like...

04:03.917 --> 04:05.625
That's, like,
Mariah Carey big.

04:05.625 --> 04:07.834
- All right, not that big, but--
- Jesus, that's still big!

04:07.834 --> 04:09.709
I don't know.

04:09.709 --> 04:10.750
It looked big to me,

04:10.750 --> 04:13.625
and it...
sparkled a lot.

04:16.542 --> 04:18.333
I'm so sorry.

04:24.750 --> 04:26.083
How long?

04:26.083 --> 04:27.208
Have they been engaged?

04:27.208 --> 04:28.792
How long have you known?

04:29.750 --> 04:31.917
Not long.

04:31.917 --> 04:33.000
How long?

04:33.000 --> 04:36.709
Uh, hmm...

04:36.709 --> 04:38.250
A week.

04:38.250 --> 04:41.083
A week?

04:41.083 --> 04:43.000
You've known for a week?

04:43.000 --> 04:44.625
I wanted to tell you.

04:44.625 --> 04:46.333
I felt so awful.

04:46.333 --> 04:47.417
Aww.

04:47.417 --> 04:50.250
- Seriously, AJ.
- Come on, AJ.

04:50.875 --> 04:51.834
Look.

04:51.834 --> 04:54.166
I get it.

04:54.166 --> 04:56.792
But it's Merc
who's the villain here.

04:56.792 --> 04:58.792
Don't be mad at me.
Be mad at him.

04:58.792 --> 05:00.458
I think...
yeah...

05:00.458 --> 05:04.250
I think there's enough mad
for both of you.

05:04.250 --> 05:06.583
Well, be madder at him.

05:06.583 --> 05:07.458
A week?

05:09.583 --> 05:10.792
Well, don't--

05:10.792 --> 05:11.583
You know,
if you're ever

05:11.583 --> 05:13.834
just sittin'
around, thinkin',

05:13.834 --> 05:16.083
"What are the cruelest
things I never got to do?"

05:16.083 --> 05:17.458
Off your bucket list.

05:20.250 --> 05:21.959
Jesus, AJ!

05:21.959 --> 05:26.959
♪♪♪

05:26.959 --> 05:28.458
[Sean] Right.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.208
Is there anything
we've talked about so far

05:30.208 --> 05:31.000
that we actually like?

05:31.000 --> 05:32.125
Anything worth pursuing?

05:32.125 --> 05:33.625
I still like Whores.

05:35.000 --> 05:36.750
So Netflix is doing it.
So what?

05:36.750 --> 05:40.000
There were two Capotes.
Two Steve Jobs.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.834
Are you really comparing
Truman Capote and Steve Jobs

05:42.834 --> 05:44.375
to Whores?

05:44.375 --> 05:45.667
No, you're right.

05:45.667 --> 05:46.333
I'd watch Whores.

05:46.333 --> 05:48.875
They're already doing it.

05:48.875 --> 05:51.250
Fuckin' Netflix.

05:51.250 --> 05:52.458
It's just crazy to invest

05:52.458 --> 05:53.834
all our time in a show

05:53.834 --> 05:54.667
that's already being done.

05:54.667 --> 05:56.625
Yeah, yeah.

05:56.625 --> 05:57.333
[sighs]

05:57.333 --> 06:00.375
I just like Whores  so much.

06:01.250 --> 06:04.375
[phone ringing]

06:06.166 --> 06:07.375
My father's girlfriend.

06:07.375 --> 06:09.083
Just ignore it.

06:09.083 --> 06:10.667
Okay, so--

06:10.667 --> 06:11.667
Maybe it's important.

06:12.792 --> 06:15.709
Pain in the ass.
Yo.

06:15.709 --> 06:18.041
[Linda] So, I'm sitting in
the kitchen with your father,

06:18.041 --> 06:19.125
and I say to him,
"Do you want lunch?

06:19.125 --> 06:21.208
I've got egg salad.

06:21.208 --> 06:22.333
I've got tuna salad."

06:22.333 --> 06:23.375
And he says,

06:23.375 --> 06:25.834
"I don't like your tuna salad."

06:25.834 --> 06:27.792
So I go,
"Since when?

06:27.792 --> 06:29.041
You love my tuna salad."

06:29.041 --> 06:29.792
And he says,

06:29.792 --> 06:31.500
"Not since you started using

06:31.500 --> 06:33.375
that shitty light mayonnaise."

06:33.375 --> 06:34.959
- Linda--
- Let me finish.

06:34.959 --> 06:36.542
So he says,
"I'm not eating it

06:36.542 --> 06:37.959
with that crap in it."

06:37.959 --> 06:38.667
So we get in the car,

06:38.667 --> 06:40.125
we schlepp over to Target--

06:40.125 --> 06:41.125
- Linda!
- What?

06:41.125 --> 06:43.542
Is there a point to this?

06:43.542 --> 06:45.333
He's dead.

06:46.792 --> 06:49.041
- What?
- He's dead.

06:49.041 --> 06:51.291
- Dear Lord.
- Oh, my God.

06:51.291 --> 06:54.709
- Wait, my father is dead?
- Dead.

06:54.709 --> 06:56.333
So, he's picking up
a jar of mayonnaise.

06:56.333 --> 06:58.375
One of those stupid big ones.

06:58.375 --> 07:00.709
Even if he lived,
he'd be dead

07:00.709 --> 07:01.500
by the time
we finished that thing.

07:01.500 --> 07:03.917
And all of a sudden,
he goes--

07:03.917 --> 07:04.917
[making phlegmatic sound]

07:04.917 --> 07:07.959
The jar drops.
There's mayonnaise everywhere.

07:07.959 --> 07:10.417
He just falls over,
and I'm thinking,

07:10.417 --> 07:12.041
"Now we're gonna
have to pay for that."

07:13.917 --> 07:16.250
- Dead?
- [Linda] Yes! Dead!

07:16.250 --> 07:18.083
Why is this so difficult?

07:18.083 --> 07:19.583
- So where is he now?
- I don't know.

07:19.583 --> 07:22.333
The ambulance people came
and took him away.

07:22.333 --> 07:23.917
- Where?
- How do I know?

07:23.917 --> 07:26.834
- They just took him.
- Jesus Christ.

07:26.834 --> 07:29.000
[Linda]
Oh, and the best part is,

07:29.000 --> 07:30.542
I'm stuck here now.

07:30.542 --> 07:32.208
What?

07:32.208 --> 07:33.917
Yeah, the car keys
were in his pocket.

07:33.917 --> 07:35.834
[Linda] So now he's dead,

07:35.834 --> 07:38.458
and I'm standing here
at Target like a schmuck.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.583
What--so did they
say what we do now?

07:40.583 --> 07:43.875
What we do now is
you come and pick me up!

07:43.875 --> 07:44.792
I'm not coming to pick you up.

07:44.792 --> 07:47.208
I got to find his body.
Call a cab.

07:47.208 --> 07:48.500
I can't call a cab.

07:48.500 --> 07:50.250
He had the money.
I have no money.

07:50.250 --> 07:51.458
Who are you?
The Queen?

07:51.458 --> 07:53.458
How do you leave
the house without money?

07:53.458 --> 07:55.750
Next time,
I'll remember to bring my wallet

07:55.750 --> 07:57.458
in case my husband drops dead

07:57.458 --> 07:59.959
and leaves me
stranded at Target.

07:59.959 --> 08:00.625
He's not your husband.

08:00.625 --> 08:02.625
Oh, go fuck yourself, okay?

08:02.625 --> 08:03.959
Just go fuck yourself.

08:03.959 --> 08:05.959
This is the worst
day of my life!

08:05.959 --> 08:07.917
Yeah. Yeah.

08:07.917 --> 08:09.792
I'll try to track him down.
Hang on.

08:09.792 --> 08:11.041
Call her an Uber.

08:11.041 --> 08:13.417
- I got to do this.
- Of course.

08:14.291 --> 08:15.959
Hello, Mrs. LeBlanc--

08:15.959 --> 08:16.667
She's not Mrs. LeBlanc.

08:16.667 --> 08:18.583
Tell him to go fuck himself.

08:18.583 --> 08:19.166
As often as I can.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.333
[Linda] Who is this?

08:21.333 --> 08:22.500
Actually, we've met.

08:22.500 --> 08:24.667
This is Beverly Lincoln.

08:24.667 --> 08:26.000
The one with the hair?

08:26.000 --> 08:28.375
That could certainly be me.

08:28.375 --> 08:30.333
[Linda] What do you want?

08:30.333 --> 08:32.083
Matt has asked us
to help you get home.

08:32.083 --> 08:33.917
Where are you?

08:35.166 --> 08:36.667
In condiments.

08:38.000 --> 08:39.917
No, I mean, where is
the store situated?

08:39.917 --> 08:41.667
We need to give them
the coordinates.

08:41.667 --> 08:44.625
Oh, I remember you now.

08:44.625 --> 08:47.333
[Linda] I'm at Target.

08:47.333 --> 08:48.709
Okay, which Target?

08:48.709 --> 08:50.041
[Linda] La Cienega.

08:50.041 --> 08:51.667
The Target on La Cienega.

08:51.667 --> 08:52.583
I heard her.

08:52.583 --> 08:55.333
Okay, go wait
in front of the store.

08:55.333 --> 08:57.333
- We're gonna get you an Uber.
- A what?

08:57.333 --> 08:59.000
- An Uber.
- An ubah?

08:59.000 --> 09:00.542
- An Uber.
- An ubah?

09:00.542 --> 09:03.625
[Linda] Say it
without the accent.

09:03.625 --> 09:06.625
- [American accent] Uber.
- [Linda] Oh, Jesus.

09:06.625 --> 09:08.792
I'm gonna turn
you over to Sean.

09:08.792 --> 09:10.250
He can give you the details.

09:10.250 --> 09:12.375
Hello, Mrs. LeBlanc.

09:12.375 --> 09:14.208
She's not Mrs. LeBlanc!

09:14.208 --> 09:15.333
[Linda] Fuck you!

09:15.333 --> 09:17.208
Your driver's name is Amjad.

09:17.208 --> 09:19.709
- What?
- Amjad.

09:19.709 --> 09:20.917
- Amjad?
- Amjad.

09:20.917 --> 09:24.208
- That's a person?
- He'll be there in six minutes.

09:24.208 --> 09:25.917
- How do you know?
- It's on my phone.

09:25.917 --> 09:28.458
- I'm on your phone.
- I have another phone.

09:28.458 --> 09:30.000
Who has two phones?

09:30.000 --> 09:31.583
No, I--
don't--

09:31.583 --> 09:34.500
The point is
your Uber driver, Amjad--

09:34.500 --> 09:35.667
Ubah.
Amjad.

09:35.667 --> 09:36.959
[Linda] Just put Matt on.

09:36.959 --> 09:38.458
Just put him back on!

09:38.458 --> 09:39.333
Hang on.

09:41.417 --> 09:42.750
All right, I found the body.

09:42.750 --> 09:45.583
Now I got to get a funeral
home to go pick it up.

09:45.583 --> 09:47.166
She's insisting
on speaking to you.

09:47.166 --> 09:48.834
She doesn't seem
to understand Uber,

09:48.834 --> 09:50.458
and she has issues
with her driver Amjad.

09:50.458 --> 09:52.250
She's clearly distraught.

09:52.250 --> 09:54.458
Let me handle it.

09:54.458 --> 09:55.083
Linda.

09:55.083 --> 09:56.917
Take the fucking Uber.

09:56.917 --> 09:56.959
Done.

10:01.083 --> 10:02.125
I'm so sorry.

10:02.125 --> 10:03.750
Yeah, she's a pain in the ass.

10:03.750 --> 10:05.208
No, about your father.

10:05.208 --> 10:08.291
Oh.
That.

10:08.291 --> 10:08.834
Well, what're you gonna do?

10:10.959 --> 10:15.709
So, we'll get out of your hair
and let you deal with this.

10:15.709 --> 10:18.000
No, no, no. Stay.
I just need, like, a second.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.583
Then we can get back to work.

10:20.500 --> 10:22.583
[Assistant] Matt LeBlanc on one.

10:22.583 --> 10:23.709
Hey, bud.
What's up?

10:23.709 --> 10:24.750
[Matt] Hey, uh...

10:24.750 --> 10:26.500
My father just died.

10:26.500 --> 10:29.250
- Aw, no.
- Dropped dead at Target.

10:29.250 --> 10:31.792
Oh! Jesus, that is sad
on so many levels.

10:31.792 --> 10:32.875
[Matt] So I, uh,

10:32.875 --> 10:35.125
I need a funeral home to go and
pick up the body.

10:35.125 --> 10:36.750
- Can you--
- [Roger] I'm on it.

10:36.750 --> 10:37.959
Text me the info,
and if there's

10:37.959 --> 10:39.125
anything else I can--

10:39.125 --> 10:40.750
Yeah, get me a Marvel franchise.

10:40.750 --> 10:42.208
[laughs]
One thing at a time.

10:42.208 --> 10:44.208
[scoffs]

10:44.208 --> 10:46.458
Okay, where were we?

10:46.458 --> 10:48.792
Are you sure
you're up for this?

10:48.792 --> 10:50.250
Sure, yeah, why not?

10:50.250 --> 10:52.959
Well, I'm sorry,
but you just lost your father.

10:52.959 --> 10:55.750
You must be feeling...
something.

10:55.750 --> 10:56.375
I feel stuff.

10:56.375 --> 10:58.583
I feel annoyed...

10:58.583 --> 11:00.750
that I have to
handle this shit.

11:00.750 --> 11:02.125
I feel relieved...

11:02.125 --> 11:03.959
that stupid Linda's
off the phone.

11:03.959 --> 11:05.625
I feel angry...

11:05.625 --> 11:05.834
at Netflix.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.375
And I'm also
a little hungry.

11:09.375 --> 11:10.000
Probably all that
mayonnaise talk.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.667
Anyone want a sandwich?

11:11.667 --> 11:14.000
You're not really eating
mayonnaise now?

11:14.000 --> 11:16.166
Yep.

11:16.166 --> 11:19.125
I'm gonna look death
in the face...

11:19.125 --> 11:21.125
and then I'm gonna
spread it on whole wheat

11:21.125 --> 11:21.625
with some turkey and Swiss.

11:21.625 --> 11:24.083
[keys clacking]

11:24.083 --> 11:26.166
I've got to say,
so far today,

11:26.166 --> 11:27.417
this is the best
idea you've had.

11:27.417 --> 11:30.291
It's the mayonnaise.

11:32.667 --> 11:33.959
Let's say

11:33.959 --> 11:36.500
you could turn on
your TV right now

11:36.500 --> 11:37.959
and watch anything
you wanted.

11:37.959 --> 11:39.500
What would it be?

11:39.500 --> 11:40.375
- And it can't be Whores.
- Oh.

11:40.375 --> 11:43.250
Anything at all.

11:45.834 --> 11:48.667
- Hmm.
- What?

11:48.667 --> 11:50.375
I should probably
call my mother.

11:50.375 --> 11:51.750
Really? Now?
When we're on a roll?

11:51.750 --> 11:54.583
Yeah, well,
I should let her know.

11:54.583 --> 11:56.208
Technically,
they're still married.

11:56.208 --> 11:57.583
- You're joking.
- Nope.

11:57.583 --> 11:59.375
40 years she wouldn't
give him a divorce.

11:59.375 --> 12:02.750
She was all about
"till death do us part."

12:02.750 --> 12:03.542
So today's quite the payoff.

12:03.542 --> 12:07.041
Just two seconds.
Keep going.

12:07.041 --> 12:09.917
[phone ringing]

12:14.709 --> 12:16.417
- Hello?
- Ma?

12:16.417 --> 12:17.291
- Hello?
- Ma?

12:17.291 --> 12:19.208
- Hello?
- Ma.

12:19.208 --> 12:20.375
Put your hearing aids in.

12:20.375 --> 12:21.333
Put your hearing aids in.

12:21.333 --> 12:25.166
Hold on, I'm putting
my hearing aids in.

12:26.792 --> 12:27.834
[feedback whines]

12:27.834 --> 12:28.625
Hello?

12:28.625 --> 12:29.917
Ma.
Feedback.

12:29.917 --> 12:31.250
[Mrs. LeBlanc] Hold on.

12:31.250 --> 12:31.875
I can't hear.

12:31.875 --> 12:34.000
[Matt] Feedback. Ma?

12:34.000 --> 12:35.750
I hate these damn things.

12:35.750 --> 12:37.333
[Matt] Ma?

12:39.333 --> 12:41.458
- Hello?
- Can you hear me now?

12:41.458 --> 12:43.041
- Hello?
- Ma?

12:43.041 --> 12:45.834
- I took it out.
- Put it back.

12:48.250 --> 12:50.583
[feedback whining]

12:50.583 --> 12:51.750
Hold on.

12:51.750 --> 12:53.834
Jesus Christ.
Adjust it.

12:53.834 --> 12:53.959
Adjust it!

12:56.917 --> 12:59.667
- Better?
- Yeah. Yeah, better.

12:59.667 --> 13:00.500
Huh.

13:00.500 --> 13:02.375
So, what's new?

13:02.375 --> 13:03.959
Dad's dead.

13:06.583 --> 13:08.250
- [Mrs. LeBlanc] What?
- [Matt] He's dead.

13:08.250 --> 13:09.500
What?

13:09.500 --> 13:10.542
- [Matt] Dead.

13:10.542 --> 13:12.166
[Sean] He's so shut down.

13:12.166 --> 13:14.458
You're assuming there's
something there to shut.

13:14.458 --> 13:15.500
You saw what they
were like together.

13:15.500 --> 13:16.792
[indistinct conversation]

13:16.792 --> 13:18.333
No, I know,
but it's his father.

13:18.333 --> 13:20.417
[phone ringing]

13:20.417 --> 13:21.000
- Linda.
- Fuck.

13:21.000 --> 13:22.959
I can't do it.
I can't.

13:22.959 --> 13:26.458
- I was last up.
- Oohh. [frustrated exhale]

13:26.458 --> 13:27.959
Fine, fine, fine, fine.

13:27.959 --> 13:30.166
Argh!
Hello.

13:30.166 --> 13:31.875
What's-his-name's
still not here yet.

13:31.875 --> 13:35.417
Hang on.
That's Sean's department.

13:36.458 --> 13:37.625
Hello, Linda.

13:37.625 --> 13:39.250
[Linda] He's still not here.

13:39.250 --> 13:41.959
- Hang on, let me check.
- I'm starting to melt.

13:41.959 --> 13:43.667
- It says he should be there.
- Well, tell it he's not.

13:43.667 --> 13:45.500
- He's in a Kia.
- IKEA?

13:45.500 --> 13:47.834
I told you Target!

13:47.834 --> 13:51.750
- Target!
- He's in a Kia.

13:51.750 --> 13:53.500
- A what?
- A Kia.

13:53.500 --> 13:56.000
- A Kia?
- A Kia.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.083
A Kia?

13:57.083 --> 13:57.583
Hang on.
Let me call him.

13:57.583 --> 13:59.166
Here's Beverly.

14:01.000 --> 14:01.375
Hello again.

14:01.375 --> 14:04.333
Ugh.

14:04.333 --> 14:06.083
Hello, Amjad?

14:06.083 --> 14:08.792
What type of Kia is it?

14:08.792 --> 14:10.959
It's a white Kia Rio.

14:10.959 --> 14:12.792
It's a white Kia Rio.

14:12.792 --> 14:15.250
- A Kiario?
- No.

14:15.250 --> 14:19.333
The model of the Kia is a Rio,

14:19.333 --> 14:20.750
and the color is white.

14:20.750 --> 14:23.500
Do you see a white car?

14:23.500 --> 14:24.709
Yeah.

14:24.709 --> 14:26.250
I'm standing
right next to one.

14:26.250 --> 14:27.083
Wave to her.

14:28.917 --> 14:30.333
That's a Kia Rio?

14:30.333 --> 14:32.000
Yes, that's a Kia Rio,

14:32.000 --> 14:33.875
- and the gentleman--
- [Linda] Oh, Jesus.

14:33.875 --> 14:34.834
I have no key.

14:34.834 --> 14:36.542
He had the keys in his pocket.

14:36.542 --> 14:37.792
I can't get into the house.

14:37.792 --> 14:40.166
I'm not sure what to tell you.

14:40.166 --> 14:41.959
God damn it.
Tell Matt I'm locked out.

14:41.959 --> 14:43.792
I need his key.

14:43.792 --> 14:45.041
I'm afraid he's on
with his mother.

14:45.041 --> 14:47.834
- Is she locked out?
- I don't think so.

14:47.834 --> 14:50.750
Then fuck her.
Just put him on.

14:50.750 --> 14:52.542
Hang on.

14:52.542 --> 14:53.542
[Matt] I just wanted you
to know.

14:53.542 --> 14:55.041
- [Linda] I don't know.
- I'm so sorry.

14:55.041 --> 14:56.375
It's, uh, Linda.

14:56.375 --> 14:57.500
[Linda speaks
indistinctly on phone]

14:57.500 --> 14:58.917
She says she's locked out
and she needs your key.

14:58.917 --> 15:00.291
I don't have a key.

15:00.291 --> 15:01.208
[Linda]
How do you not have a key?

15:01.208 --> 15:02.750
How do you not have a key?

15:02.750 --> 15:04.500
- You live there.
- Would you like the phone?

15:04.500 --> 15:06.166
No, call in a fucking locksmith.

15:06.166 --> 15:07.625
Absolutely.

15:07.625 --> 15:08.875
It only gets better.

15:08.875 --> 15:11.083
[Mrs. LeBlanc]
Get who a locksmith?

15:11.083 --> 15:11.375
Linda.

15:11.375 --> 15:12.375
Who?

15:12.375 --> 15:14.917
Linda.

15:14.917 --> 15:16.750
I don't believe I know
anyone by that name.

15:16.750 --> 15:18.166
All right, Ma.

15:18.166 --> 15:19.750
Ooh, that whore.

15:19.750 --> 15:22.083
Anyway, that's the news.

15:22.083 --> 15:23.333
[Mrs. LeBlanc]
Whoa, whoa, whoa, wait,

15:23.333 --> 15:24.542
how's he getting back here?

15:24.542 --> 15:25.250
- Who?
- Your father, who.

15:25.250 --> 15:26.834
- For what?
- His funeral.

15:26.834 --> 15:29.834
- What funeral?
- "What funeral?"

15:29.834 --> 15:33.041
After everything
that asshole did?

15:33.041 --> 15:34.583
He's still my husband.

15:34.583 --> 15:37.000
I get to put him in the ground.

15:37.917 --> 15:39.417
Fine, I'll...

15:39.417 --> 15:41.917
I'll figure out a way
to ship him back.

15:41.917 --> 15:42.834
Good.

15:42.834 --> 15:44.417
Now, I got to go to Costco.

15:44.417 --> 15:45.250
- What should I get you?
- For what?

15:45.250 --> 15:47.375
Well, you're
coming in for this.

15:47.375 --> 15:48.834
- No, I'm not.
- He's your father.

15:48.834 --> 15:50.625
How's it gonna look?

15:50.625 --> 15:53.417
How'd it look 40 years ago
when he walked out on us?

15:53.417 --> 15:54.542
Oh, let it go, Matthew.

15:54.542 --> 15:56.583
He's dead.

15:56.583 --> 15:58.291
He's with God.

15:58.291 --> 16:00.333
I doubt that.

16:00.333 --> 16:01.417
[Merc] Hello?

16:01.417 --> 16:03.750
- In here!
- Hey, babe.

16:03.750 --> 16:08.125
So, I've got some big news.

16:08.125 --> 16:09.291
Big big?

16:09.291 --> 16:11.083
Oh, pretty darn big.

16:11.083 --> 16:12.417
Hmm.
Intriguing.

16:12.417 --> 16:16.792
Guess who's engaged
to Morning Randolph?

16:20.208 --> 16:21.792
- What?
- [laughs]

16:21.792 --> 16:23.959
Obviously, no one told you,

16:23.959 --> 16:25.959
or you would've said
something to me.

16:25.959 --> 16:29.291
But I guess--
congratulations!

16:29.291 --> 16:30.250
[both laugh]

16:30.250 --> 16:32.458
Okay, that  is crazy.

16:32.458 --> 16:34.792
Seriously loony tunes crazy.

16:34.792 --> 16:36.625
Just tellin' you what I heard.

16:36.625 --> 16:38.000
- From who?
- Not important.

16:38.000 --> 16:40.125
That I am engaged
to Morning Randolph?

16:40.125 --> 16:43.291
This person was pretty sure.
She saw a ring.

16:43.291 --> 16:44.834
A ring?
Jesus.

16:44.834 --> 16:46.792
I don't even know
what to do with that.

16:46.792 --> 16:47.834
Either someone is
fucking with you,

16:47.834 --> 16:51.041
or they're just nuts.

16:51.041 --> 16:52.041
Look, I totally get
why you'd flip out.

16:52.041 --> 16:55.208
But I swear,
it is not true.

16:55.208 --> 16:58.834
I swear on the lives
of my children.

16:58.834 --> 17:01.000
First of all, engaged?

17:01.000 --> 17:02.208
Me?

17:02.208 --> 17:04.458
I'm still paying off
the first three.

17:04.458 --> 17:07.125
And if I was ever
gonna do it again,

17:07.125 --> 17:09.125
you know...
you know...

17:09.125 --> 17:10.667
I love you.

17:10.667 --> 17:14.500
And Morning Randolph?
Are you kidding me?

17:14.500 --> 17:18.000
She's been around since,
like, Truman was president.

17:18.000 --> 17:20.375
Seriously, I think
they named planes after her

17:20.375 --> 17:21.458
in World War II.

17:21.458 --> 17:22.875
I mean...

17:30.208 --> 17:32.041
Okay.

17:32.041 --> 17:32.875
Okay, this--

17:32.875 --> 17:33.208
this is not fair.

17:36.291 --> 17:39.709
Look, clearly,
I have a problem.

17:39.709 --> 17:41.750
I-I-I'm a deeply
damaged person.

17:41.750 --> 17:44.875
It's-It's a sickness.

17:44.875 --> 17:47.834
There's something
profoundly wrong with me.

17:47.834 --> 17:52.709
But it's only because of how
much I care for you both

17:52.709 --> 17:53.875
that I haven't been able to...

17:53.875 --> 17:55.291
By the way,
that stuff about

17:55.291 --> 17:57.083
the lives
of my children--

17:57.083 --> 17:58.959
that's just an expression.

17:58.959 --> 18:01.208
God knows that.

18:01.208 --> 18:03.083
And can I just say,
I don't know how much you heard,

18:03.083 --> 18:05.667
but that crap
about World War II,

18:05.667 --> 18:08.750
you know me, I just--
"blah, blah, blah."

18:08.750 --> 18:11.166
I mean, you know
how much I care for--

18:11.166 --> 18:12.917
Which is, you know,
not to take

18:12.917 --> 18:15.834
anything away from...

18:23.000 --> 18:24.375
Yeah, I got nothing.

18:27.667 --> 18:31.583
[keys clacking]

18:31.583 --> 18:32.500
All right, I'm erasing Whores.

18:32.500 --> 18:35.250
Ooh.

18:35.250 --> 18:38.000
- What about racing whores?
- What?

18:38.000 --> 18:40.417
Whores in cars, competing.

18:40.417 --> 18:41.917
both: No!

18:41.917 --> 18:42.750
Why not?

18:42.750 --> 18:43.625
Because it's not a show.

18:43.625 --> 18:45.542
Yet.

18:45.542 --> 18:46.750
[phone ringing]

18:46.750 --> 18:48.750
- Oh, come on.
- Seriously?

18:48.750 --> 18:49.875
♪ upbeat music ♪

18:49.875 --> 18:51.417
- Roger.
- Linda.

18:51.417 --> 18:53.792
- I got to do this one.
- Oh, come on.

18:53.792 --> 18:54.667
What, you think I'm having fun?

18:54.667 --> 18:57.125
Well, imagine
what it's like for us.

18:58.166 --> 19:00.875
Yo. We got to ship
the body to Boston.

19:00.875 --> 19:01.667
Your turn.

19:01.667 --> 19:02.667
[growls]

19:02.667 --> 19:04.750
Hello, Linda.

19:04.750 --> 19:06.875
There's still no locksmith.

19:06.875 --> 19:07.625
Hang on.

19:07.625 --> 19:10.458
Beverly made those arrangements.

19:13.250 --> 19:14.458
Hello again.

19:14.458 --> 19:15.291
Locksmith.

19:15.291 --> 19:16.375
Is on his way.

19:16.375 --> 19:18.333
He should be there any minute.

19:18.333 --> 19:21.959
He's from All-A Locksmith,

19:21.959 --> 19:24.792
and his name is--
God, help me--

19:24.792 --> 19:25.792
Yarl.

19:25.792 --> 19:27.917
- Yarl?
- Yarl.

19:27.917 --> 19:30.041
[Linda] No. No, no.
Put Matt on.

19:30.041 --> 19:31.667
I want to talk to Matt.

19:31.667 --> 19:33.041
I'm afraid right now
he's making arrangements

19:33.041 --> 19:34.834
to ship the body to Boston.

19:34.834 --> 19:35.667
[Linda] What?

19:35.667 --> 19:37.500
Stop him.

19:37.500 --> 19:38.500
Just put him on.

19:38.500 --> 19:40.125
God damn it, put him on!

19:42.166 --> 19:43.834
God damn it,
she wants you.

19:43.834 --> 19:46.125
I'll call you back.

19:47.083 --> 19:47.834
What?

19:47.834 --> 19:49.500
You cannot bury him.

19:49.500 --> 19:50.667
What are you talking about?

19:50.667 --> 19:52.333
He's got to be cremated.

19:52.333 --> 19:53.834
- Who says?
- [Linda] He says.

19:53.834 --> 19:55.333
He wants to be cremated,

19:55.333 --> 19:57.083
and he wants his ashes
scattered at sea.

19:57.083 --> 19:58.750
[Matt] At sea?

19:58.750 --> 20:01.709
The only thing he ever did
in the sea was piss in it.

20:01.709 --> 20:02.166
It's in his will.

20:02.166 --> 20:05.250
Fuck me.
Fine.

20:06.417 --> 20:07.834
Call Roger back.

20:07.834 --> 20:09.667
Tell him the body
needs to be cremated.

20:09.667 --> 20:11.208
Pain in my ass.

20:13.709 --> 20:16.542
[phone ringing]

20:19.083 --> 20:19.917
[feedback whining]
Hello?

20:19.917 --> 20:21.834
- Adjust.
- What?

20:21.834 --> 20:24.542
Adjust.

20:25.667 --> 20:27.041
- Better?
- Better.

20:27.041 --> 20:28.959
So, you change your mind?

20:28.959 --> 20:29.875
You coming in?

20:29.875 --> 20:31.375
No, I'm not coming,

20:31.375 --> 20:32.917
and there's not
gonna be a funeral.

20:32.917 --> 20:34.208
What does that mean?

20:34.208 --> 20:36.250
Apparently,
he wants to be cremated.

20:36.250 --> 20:37.417
[Mrs. LeBlanc] He wants?

20:37.417 --> 20:39.000
Who cares what he wants?

20:39.000 --> 20:40.875
For once,
let him do what I want.

20:40.875 --> 20:42.500
- It's in his will.
- [Mrs. LeBlanc] Oh, Jesus.

20:42.500 --> 20:45.583
So what am I supposed to do
with the casket?

20:45.583 --> 20:46.875
What casket?

20:46.875 --> 20:48.083
I just bought
a casket at Costco.

20:48.083 --> 20:50.583
They sell caskets at Costco?

20:50.583 --> 20:53.250
- Next to the tires.
- So just return it.

20:53.250 --> 20:54.875
What if they won't take it back?

20:54.875 --> 20:56.542
What am I supposed
to do with it?

20:56.542 --> 20:58.250
I don't know.
Stick it in the garage.

20:58.250 --> 20:58.792
You're gonna need it eventually.

20:58.792 --> 21:00.333
[phone rings]

21:00.333 --> 21:02.917
- Hello?
- [Linda] Get me Matt.

21:02.917 --> 21:05.583
Tell him it's about the ashes.

21:05.583 --> 21:06.917
[Mrs. LeBlanc] Cherry poplar

21:06.917 --> 21:07.709
with a champagne velvet
interior.

21:07.709 --> 21:08.500
Guess who?

21:08.500 --> 21:11.208
She wants to talk
about the ashes.

21:11.208 --> 21:11.959
What?

21:11.959 --> 21:13.959
When am I getting them?

21:13.959 --> 21:15.625
[Mrs. LeBlanc] That whore's
not getting the ashes.

21:15.625 --> 21:18.250
- Those are my ashes!
- [Matt] Why do you get 'em?

21:18.250 --> 21:20.417
I thought they were supposed
to be scattered at sea.

21:20.417 --> 21:21.917
[Mrs. LeBlanc] At sea?

21:21.917 --> 21:22.750
What is he, a Kennedy?

21:22.750 --> 21:25.208
I'm supposed to be
the scatterer!

21:25.208 --> 21:26.917
[Mrs. LeBlanc] Bullshit!

21:26.917 --> 21:27.917
He's my husband.

21:27.917 --> 21:31.250
You keep your hands off him.
We got water here.

21:31.250 --> 21:33.709
- [Mrs. LeBlanc] I'm scattering.
- [Linda] I'm scattering.

21:33.709 --> 21:36.041
[Mrs. LeBlanc] Bullshit!
I'm scattering! I'm scattering!

21:36.041 --> 21:37.417
It's Roger.
There's a problem.

21:37.417 --> 21:38.417
- Oh, God. Hold on!
- [Linda] Fuck you.

21:38.417 --> 21:40.083
[Mrs. LeBlanc]
You whore, fuck you.

21:40.083 --> 21:41.667
What?

21:41.667 --> 21:43.458
[Roger] I just got off
with the mortuary.

21:43.458 --> 21:46.625
They can't cremate him
for at least a couple of weeks.

21:46.625 --> 21:47.750
Weeks?

21:47.750 --> 21:49.000
Apparently, there's
some big backlog.

21:49.000 --> 21:50.417
Did you play the Friends  card?

21:50.417 --> 21:51.792
[Roger] Of course
I played the Friends  card.

21:51.792 --> 21:52.792
I offered them tickets
to the The Box.

21:52.792 --> 21:54.959
I said you would take
a picture with them.

21:54.959 --> 21:57.041
- Well, let's not go crazy.
- They did tell me--

21:57.041 --> 21:58.458
And this is
totally off the record--

21:58.458 --> 22:01.834
There might be
a little bit of wiggle room

22:01.834 --> 22:05.417
if the ashes...
don't have to be his.

22:05.417 --> 22:08.375
Well, shit, if they don't
have to be his...

22:08.375 --> 22:09.500
[doorbell rings]

22:09.500 --> 22:12.792
- [Beverly] Doorbell.
- Oh, can you let him in?

22:12.792 --> 22:14.917
It's the guy from
the prop house.

22:18.333 --> 22:20.583
Hey, thanks so much
for doing this.

22:20.583 --> 22:22.250
Hey. For you?
Pfft.

22:22.250 --> 22:23.333
- Wow, these look great.
- They should.

22:23.333 --> 22:25.500
This one was used
in Harold and Maude.

22:25.500 --> 22:26.417
It was also in
the first Godfather.

22:26.417 --> 22:28.792
- Terms of Endearment.
- Wow.

22:28.792 --> 22:30.542
It's got better
credits than you.

22:30.542 --> 22:31.250
The other one's mostly done TV.

22:31.250 --> 22:33.375
It started off in Quincy.

22:33.375 --> 22:35.208
- You remember--
- Jack Klugman. Sure.

22:35.208 --> 22:36.375
[Matt] Well, they look great.

22:36.375 --> 22:38.000
And they're for what again?

22:38.000 --> 22:39.500
I'm helping my nephew out
with a student film thing.

22:39.500 --> 22:42.625
- Ah-huh. You're a good uncle.
- [scoffs]

22:42.625 --> 22:44.500
I need them back
in, like, two weeks.

22:44.500 --> 22:45.000
Yeah. Absolutely.
No problem.

22:45.000 --> 22:46.792
Thanks again.

22:49.041 --> 22:49.792
You're never gonna
return those.

22:49.792 --> 22:51.333
What, are they
gonna arrest me?

22:51.333 --> 22:52.083
Come on.
Steaks are getting cold.

22:52.083 --> 22:55.834
[keys clacking]

22:55.834 --> 22:57.041
It's weird.

22:57.041 --> 22:59.208
Every time I make a steak,
I think about my father.

22:59.208 --> 23:02.834
Like a big, thick, juicy...

23:02.834 --> 23:05.375
you know, the kind of steak
even a cow would go,

23:05.375 --> 23:07.959
"Nope, that's fair.
I totally get it."

23:07.959 --> 23:09.291
And why your father?

23:09.291 --> 23:12.208
He made me my first great steak.

23:12.208 --> 23:14.250
I was, like, five,

23:14.250 --> 23:15.250
and he came home
with this big box

23:15.250 --> 23:18.375
of these unbelievable rib eyes.

23:18.375 --> 23:20.959
He got 'em from my "Uncle" Lou.

23:20.959 --> 23:23.500
Apparently, the box had
"fallen off the truck."

23:25.375 --> 23:28.125
These steaks were
so fucking amazing.

23:28.125 --> 23:29.583
Well, there you go.

23:29.583 --> 23:31.250
So your father did do
something positive.

23:31.250 --> 23:33.208
Yeah, wait.

23:33.208 --> 23:35.041
After dinner,
I go to give our dog Tippy

23:35.041 --> 23:36.500
one of the bones.

23:36.500 --> 23:38.709
[gasps] Do not tell me
you were eating Tippy.

23:38.709 --> 23:40.709
What? No.
Jesus.

23:40.709 --> 23:41.583
Sorry, but
the way you said it.

23:41.583 --> 23:44.542
- No, I went there too.
- [Matt] No!

23:44.542 --> 23:47.959
My father traded Tippy
for the box of steaks.

23:47.959 --> 23:49.375
But he was alive.

23:49.375 --> 23:51.250
He gave away my dog.

23:51.250 --> 23:53.000
You were five.
Who does that?

23:53.000 --> 23:54.250
Yeah, no, obviously
it's terrible.

23:54.250 --> 23:55.166
- Ohh!
- Stop being relieved!

23:55.166 --> 23:56.709
No, I get it.

23:56.709 --> 23:57.208
Yeah, yeah, totally.

23:57.208 --> 24:00.834
[keys clacking]

24:00.834 --> 24:01.959
Is no one else troubled
by this at all?

24:01.959 --> 24:04.125
What?

24:04.125 --> 24:06.041
You're making two ladies
very happy.

24:06.041 --> 24:08.750
And hopefully
they stop fucking calling.

24:08.750 --> 24:12.250
And you don't worry they'll
notice a vague sirloin-y aroma?

24:12.250 --> 24:14.750
Hey, if they're sniffing
a dead guy's ashes,

24:14.750 --> 24:16.166
they got bigger problems.

24:19.166 --> 24:23.125
So did your father really
do nothing good? At all?

24:23.125 --> 24:25.041
Not one nice memory?

24:26.166 --> 24:28.333
He once took us
to Disney World.

24:28.333 --> 24:29.709
- Well, okay.
- That's something.

24:29.709 --> 24:32.250
Except he didn't want to wait
in any of the lines,

24:32.250 --> 24:34.291
so he gets this
used child's wheelchair.

24:34.291 --> 24:35.625
- Come on!
- He did not.

24:35.625 --> 24:37.000
Then he shaved my head.

24:37.000 --> 24:38.291
- No.
- Oh, stop it.

24:38.291 --> 24:40.291
Swear to God.
I got pictures with Mickey.

24:42.208 --> 24:43.792
You realize that's your show.

24:43.792 --> 24:45.166
What's my show?

24:45.166 --> 24:48.125
The father is a con man.

24:48.125 --> 24:49.750
Shifty.
Conniving.

24:49.750 --> 24:50.959
But still charming.

24:50.959 --> 24:52.709
You thought
my father was charming?

24:52.709 --> 24:53.959
- Mm-hmm.
- In his way.

24:53.959 --> 24:56.000
Twinkle in his eye.
But still a bastard.

24:56.000 --> 24:58.792
The son is very different.
Let's say he's a cop.

24:58.792 --> 25:03.458
Maybe a detective who goes
after people like his father.

25:03.458 --> 25:04.875
Right.

25:04.875 --> 25:07.166
And it's all about their
incredibly complicated

25:07.166 --> 25:07.917
love/hate/hate/hate
relationship.

25:07.917 --> 25:09.834
[laughs]

25:09.834 --> 25:11.041
I kind of like that.

25:11.041 --> 25:13.000
I could see me playing a cop.

25:13.000 --> 25:14.083
Oh, no, no, no.
No, you're the father.

25:14.083 --> 25:17.291
What? No fuckin' way.
I'm not playing that asshole.

25:17.291 --> 25:20.083
It's the better part.

25:20.083 --> 25:21.750
Yeah, I'm the father.

25:21.750 --> 25:24.750
[keys clacking]

25:24.750 --> 25:27.625
[doorbell rings]

25:30.875 --> 25:33.291
Hey.

25:33.291 --> 25:34.917
So, the guy from
the mortuary called back.

25:34.917 --> 25:39.000
Turns out, uh, his wife's
a big fan of your show.

25:39.000 --> 25:39.709
- Yeah?
- Promised him a ton of tickets.

25:39.709 --> 25:41.667
VIP tour.
The whole deal.

25:41.667 --> 25:43.583
You will have to take a picture.

25:43.583 --> 25:45.250
Fine.

25:45.250 --> 25:48.542
But it got your dad bumped
to the front of the line.

25:48.542 --> 25:50.542
They did him this afternoon.

25:52.625 --> 25:55.208
- This is him?
- This is him.

25:55.208 --> 25:57.500
[exasperated sigh]

25:59.291 --> 26:03.250
- Jesus.
- Yeah.

26:03.250 --> 26:05.417
- He's heavy.
- I know.

26:07.083 --> 26:10.333
- You want a drink or something?
- I'm late for a dinner.

26:10.333 --> 26:11.417
- With who?
- Just a client.

26:11.417 --> 26:12.875
- Who?
- A client.

26:12.875 --> 26:15.792
- Bradley Cooper?
- Why do you do this?

26:15.792 --> 26:16.208
I love you, bud.

26:16.208 --> 26:18.208
All right?

26:27.250 --> 26:30.208
[indistinct sports
announcements on TV]

